## Major in Computer Science (12 Courses)

The major in Computer Science requires the successful completion of the following:

- A minimum of **12 courses / 48 credits**
- A minimum grade point average of **2.0**
- Only grades of **"C" or higher** are applicable to our majors and minors (and the required prerequisites)

### Core Requirements (7)

| Course | Title | Semester | Prerequisite |
|---|---|---|---|
| CSCI-UA.0101 | Introduction to Computer Science | Fall / Spring | CSCI-UA.0002 or CSCI-UA.0003 or placement exam |
| CSCI-UA.0102 | Data Structures | Fall / Spring | CSCI-UA.0101 |
| CSCI-UA.0201 | Computer Systems Organization | Fall / Spring | CSCI-UA.0102 |
| CSCI-UA.0202 | Operating Systems | Fall / Spring | CSCI-UA.0201 |
| CSCI-UA.0310 | Basic Algorithms | Fall / Spring | Data Structures (CSCI-UA 102), Discrete Mathematics (MATH-UA 120) and Calculus I (MATH-UA 121) or Math for Economics I (MATH-UA 131) |
| MATH-UA.0121 | Calculus I | Fall / Spring / Summer | MATH-UA.0009 |
| MATH-UA.0120 | Discrete Mathematics | Fall / Spring | See prerequisites below |

#### Discrete Mathematics Prerequisites

One of the following:

- SAT score of 670 or higher on mathematics portion
- ACT/ACTE Math score of 30 or higher
- AB score of 3 or higher
- BC score of 3 or higher
- A level Maths score of C or higher (anyone who took Further Maths should contact the math department as it varies depending on the exam board)
- AS level Maths score of B or higher
- IB HL score of 5 or higher
- IB SL score of 6 or higher
- Completion of Algebra and Calculus (MATH-UA 009) with a grade of C or higher
- Passing placement exam

### Electives (5)

**FIVE electives**, numbered CSCI-UA.04xx

Electives vary every fall, spring semester and there is one elective option offered in the summer semester. Students may substitute a 400-level elective with one of the following Math classes: **MATH-UA.0122 Calculus II**, **MATH-UA.0140 Linear Algebra**, and/or **MATH-UA.0185 Probability and Statistics** — a maximum of two classes can be substituted.

