## Credit Distribution

The Computer Science Major of 12 courses/48 credits can be distributed in the following ways:

| Distribution | CS Courses (Credits) | Math Courses (Credits) | Total Credits | Ratio | % CS / % Math |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| Option 1 | 10 (40) | 2 (8) | 48 | 5 to 1 | 83% CS & 17% Math |
| Option 2 | 9 (36) | 3 (12) | 48 | 3 to 1 | 75% CS & 25% Math |
| Option 3 | 8 (32) | 4 (16) | 48 | 2 to 1 | 67% CS & 33% Math |

Students must complete a **minimum of 32 credits with the CSCI-UA designation** as part of their 48 credits for the CS major.
